Hi @Mrazator — I'd like to take this on.

**Root cause:** `packages/excalidraw/wysiwyg/textWysiwyg.tsx` sets `editable.onblur = handleSubmit`, which destroys the editor on *any* blur — including when the textarea loses focus because the window itself lost focus (Alt+Tab, switching browser tabs). Returning then requires clicking the text element again.

Plain textareas (like GitHub's comment field) don't have this problem because nothing is wired to the blur event — the browser auto-restores focus to the previously-active element when the window regains focus.

**Proposed fix:** guard the blur handler with `document.hasFocus()` — when the window itself has lost focus, skip `handleSubmit` and let the browser handle focus restoration naturally:

```ts
const handleBlur = () => {
  if (!document.hasFocus()) {
    return;
  }
  handleSubmit();
};
// ...
editable.onblur = handleBlur;
```

Minimal change, no impact on other blur paths (click outside, pointerdown on canvas, `beforeunload`, the `temporarilyDisableSubmit` edge case for property menu interactions — those keep their existing behavior).

I have the fix + a regression test (`should keep editor open when window loses focus (e.g. Alt+Tab)`) ready locally and all 71 tests in `textWysiwyg.test.tsx` still pass. Happy to open a PR once assigned.

